title.narrative: PARENTS WITH SKILLS

description.narrative: Output 1.1. Parents have developed skills related to the comprehensive development of their children from 0 to 6 years of age in the selected municipalities., which contributes to Economic And Social Policy General, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence (Covid), Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Maternal And Newborn Health, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Strategies to address cross-cutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied.

title.narrative: Output 1.1. Parents have developed skills related to the comprehensive development of their children from 0 to 6 years of age inthe selected municipalities.

description.narrative: In partnership with two indigenous municipal associations (mancomunidades) in the departments of Lempira and Intibucá, UNICEF provided 16,824 children under 5 years of age with access to vaccination services and 2,748 pregnant women with access to prenatal care, after implementing an educational process to increase maternal and child health skills among families to enable them to support their children’s comprehensive development. In response to emergencies, UNICEF provided 5,588 parents and caregivers with advice on infant and young child feeding (IYCF) and trained 1,500 families and 192 volunteers to enable them to detect acute malnutrition. | Status:Met | As-of Date:26/01/2022
